main event: Cpl Harold N. Blair, while on duty, observed a flying saucer type object fly over the post at an estimated speed of 700-800 mph.
interesting points: The object was described as 10 feet wide, had a green fluorescent appearance, and had two red flames protruding from the rear.
Blair observed the object for approximately 2 to 3 seconds before it moved out of sight.
The object was traveling from the Southwest to the Northeast and emitted a peculiar sound resembling a model airplane engine.
The report includes a drawing re-produced from Blair's sketch depicting the object with red flames and a green fluorescent flow.
The report mentions that the source does not sound credible, indicating skepticism towards the witness.
witnesses: Cpl Harold N. Blair, Military Police Company
